00:22:08.845 --> 00:22:10.511
Okay. how about this?

520
00:22:10.512 --> 00:22:13.344
I don't actually think I
owe you an explanation.

521
00:22:13.345 --> 00:22:15.886
We dated for a while.
it didn't work out.

522
00:22:15.887 --> 00:22:18.010
And now all I'm asking

523
00:22:18.011 --> 00:22:20.219
is that you keep your
mouth shut so that I can

524
00:22:20.220 --> 00:22:21.969
have a chance to win this campaign

525
00:22:21.970 --> 00:22:24.177
and make a real difference
in the lives of the children

526
00:22:24.178 --> 00:22:27.260
you purport to care so much about.

527
00:22:27.928 --> 00:22:29.345
Okay?

528
00:22:32.610 --> 00:22:33.856
Sure.

529
00:22:34.883 --> 00:22:36.362
Good luck with the campaign.

530
00:22:36.363 --> 00:22:38.243
- Thanks for the tea.
- [sighs]

531
00:22:39.236 --> 00:22:40.384
Noah. wait.

532
00:22:41.802 --> 00:22:43.386
I'm sorry.

533
00:22:44.263 --> 00:22:45.803
I didn't mean to hurt you.

534
00:22:46.161 --> 00:22:47.283
It's just that...

535
00:22:47.804 --> 00:22:49.477
Carl and I...

536
00:22:51.020 --> 00:22:52.480
have a history.

537
00:22:53.095 --> 00:22:55.913
A child. a whole life.

538
00:22:55.914 --> 00:22:58.177
Yeah. and you broke up
'cause he cheated on you.

539
00:22:58.833 --> 00:23:00.928
What makes you think this time
is gonna be any different?

540
00:23:01.713 --> 00:23:03.344
Because we're different people now.

541
00:23:04.008 --> 00:23:06.219
Look. I think when I was young. I...

542
00:23:07.342 --> 00:23:09.428
I fell in love with his potential.

543
00:23:11.450 --> 00:23:14.218
But now that I've lived
a while. I've learned

544
00:23:14.219 --> 00:23:17.261
to love him for who he actually is.

545
00:23:26.970 --> 00:23:28.929
[car horn blaring in distance]

546
00:23:43.011 --> 00:23:45.177
[Bruce Springsteen's "Tougher
than the Rest" playing]

547
00:23:45.178 --> 00:23:47.095
[indistinct crowd chatter]

548
00:23:55.470 --> 00:23:58.469
[Sasha] ♪ I been watching you a while ♪

549
00:23:58.470 --> 00:24:03.552
♪ Maybe you've been watching me. too ♪

550
00:24:03.553 --> 00:24:08.469
♪ So somebody ran out ♪

551
00:24:08.470 --> 00:24:13.594
♪ And left your heart in a mess ♪

552
00:24:13.595 --> 00:24:16.094
♪ But if you're looking for love ♪

553
00:24:16.095 --> 00:24:19.135
♪ Honey. I'm tougher ♪

554
00:24:19.136 --> 00:24:21.469
♪ Than the rest... ♪

555
00:24:21.470 --> 00:24:23.469
Hey!

556
00:24:23.470 --> 00:24:26.094
Oh. hi!

557
00:24:26.095 --> 00:24:27.803
Isn't he funny?

558
00:24:27.804 --> 00:24:29.552
♪ Or some good-lookin' Joe... ♪

559
00:24:29.553 --> 00:24:31.052
He's a terrible singer.

560
00:24:31.053 --> 00:24:32.844
Yeah. it's horrifying.

561
00:24:32.845 --> 00:24:37.844
♪ On their arm. some girl like
a sweet-talkin' Romeo... ♪

562
00:24:37.845 --> 00:24:40.719
Hey. is there something
you want to tell me?

563
00:24:40.720 --> 00:24:44.094
What? About what?

564
00:24:44.095 --> 00:24:46.511
Oh. my God. you're here!

565
00:24:46.512 --> 00:24:47.844
- Hi.
- Hi.

566
00:24:47.845 --> 00:24:50.135
- Hi. how are you?
- I'm good now.

567
00:24:50.136 --> 00:24:54.419
♪ So if you're rough enough for love ♪

568
00:24:54.420 --> 00:24:59.512
♪ Honey. I'm tougher than the rest ♪

569
00:25:00.952 --> 00:25:05.302
♪ The road is dark ♪

570
00:25:05.303 --> 00:25:07.484
♪ And it's a thin ♪

571
00:25:07.485 --> 00:25:10.636
♪ Thin line ♪

572
00:25:10.637 --> 00:25:12.260
♪ But I want you... ♪

573
00:25:12.261 --> 00:25:15.427
[woman] ♪ Are ringing ♪

574
00:25:15.428 --> 00:25:18.637
♪ For me and my gal... ♪

575
00:25:21.345 --> 00:25:23.260
- What the hell?
- Oh. this.

576
00:25:23.261 --> 00:25:25.386
Uh... this is just vitamin B.

577
00:25:25.387 --> 00:25:27.302
- What are you doing. man?
- Trying to fight a cold.

578
00:25:27.303 --> 00:25:29.386
- With Helen.
- What do you mean?

579
00:25:29.387 --> 00:25:30.928
She just lost someone. okay?

580
00:25:30.929 --> 00:25:32.702
- She's in a very fragile place.
- [stall door opens]

581
00:25:32.703 --> 00:25:34.553
So I think it'd be the
better part of valor...

582
00:25:35.512 --> 00:25:37.135
You're Sasha Mann.

583
00:25:37.136 --> 00:25:38.594
Yeah. last time I checked.

584
00:25:38.595 --> 00:25:40.094
[man] Think I could get a picture?

585
00:25:40.095 --> 00:25:41.386
[Sasha] Why don't we do this?

586
00:25:41.387 --> 00:25:44.844
Why don't you and I share a real moment

587
00:25:44.845 --> 00:25:47.761
where we sort of really
see each other. hmm?

588
00:25:47.762 --> 00:25:49.679
How does that sound?

589
00:25:50.887 --> 00:25:52.302
[clicks]

590
00:25:53.263 --> 00:25:55.430
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

591
00:25:56.887 --> 00:25:59.094
- Look. Sasha...
- You're very competitive.

592
00:25:59.095 --> 00:26:01.844
aren't you? Territorial.
About women especially.

593
00:26:01.845 --> 00:26:03.761
I saw it that morning in the café.

594
00:26:03.762 --> 00:26:05.302
I'm not territorial.

595
00:26:05.303 --> 00:26:07.386
I care about her.

596
00:26:07.387 --> 00:26:08.636
She's the mother of my children.

597
00:26:08.637 --> 00:26:10.762
- She's my best friend.
- [stall door opens]

598
00:26:13.095 --> 00:26:15.929
Whom you lied to. cheated on. and left.

599
00:26:17.595 --> 00:26:20.135
Yet I'm the one she needs
to be protected from.

600
00:26:20.830 --> 00:26:22.761
Look. it's more complicated than that.

601
00:26:22.762 --> 00:26:24.135
Please.

602
00:26:24.136 --> 00:26:26.511
See. this is why

603
00:26:26.512 --> 00:26:28.361
you don't understand the character.

604
00:26:28.362 --> 00:26:29.511
What?

605
00:26:29.512 --> 00:26:30.928
What does that mean?

606
00:26:30.929 --> 00:26:33.469
Noah. you can't see yourself.

607
00:26:33.470 --> 00:26:34.969
and you never could. and that's why

608
00:26:34.970 --> 00:26:37.844
you never get what you want.

609
00:26:37.845 --> 00:26:40.678
Now. are you going to let
me leave the men's room.

610
00:26:41.384 --> 00:26:43.470
or are we going to have a problem?

611
00:26:49.220 --> 00:26:51.303
[door opens]

612
00:26:52.970 --> 00:26:54.552
[Liz Phair's "Divorce Song" playing]

613
00:26:54.553 --> 00:26:57.344
[Helen] ♪ You put in my hands ♪

614
00:26:57.345 --> 00:27:02.302
♪ A loaded gun and then
told me not to fire it ♪

615
00:27:02.303 --> 00:27:06.844
♪ When you did the things
you said were up to me ♪

616
00:27:06.845 --> 00:27:09.928
♪ And then accused me of
trying to fuck it up ♪

617
00:27:09.929 --> 00:27:13.761
♪ But you've never been
a waste of my time ♪

618
00:27:13.762 --> 00:27:17.928
♪ It's never been a drag ♪

619
00:27:17.929 --> 00:27:22.219
♪ So take a deep breath
and count back from ten ♪

620
00:27:22.220 --> 00:27:26.344
♪ And maybe you'll be all right ♪

621
00:27:26.345 --> 00:27:30.469
♪ And the license said you
had to stick around ♪

622
00:27:30.470 --> 00:27:32.970
♪ Until I was dead ♪

623
00:27:34.720 --> 00:27:38.344
♪ But if you're tired
of looking at my face ♪

624
00:27:38.345 --> 00:27:41.719
♪ I guess I already am ♪

625
00:27:41.720 --> 00:27:44.010
♪ But you've never been a... ♪

626
00:27:44.011 --> 00:27:46.177
♪ If you come and be ♪

627
00:27:46.178 --> 00:27:49.803
♪ My sweet baby. mine ♪

628
00:27:49.804 --> 00:27:52.177
♪ Because I... ♪

629
00:27:52.178 --> 00:27:54.511
[crowd whooping]

630
00:27:54.512 --> 00:27:58.844
♪ Ain't got nobody... ♪

631
00:27:58.845 --> 00:28:01.094
[woman] What?

632
00:28:01.095 --> 00:28:05.761
♪ 'Cause nobody cares for me ♪

633
00:28:05.762 --> 00:28:07.719
[song ends]

634
00:28:07.720 --> 00:28:10.844
[applause and cheering]

635
00:28:10.845 --> 00:28:12.344
[indistinct chatter]

636
00:28:12.345 --> 00:28:13.886
Okay. Erica. Erica.

637
00:28:13.887 --> 00:28:15.260
you are next.

638
00:28:15.261 --> 00:28:17.594
Here she comes. All right. Erica.

639
00:28:17.595 --> 00:28:19.803
Let's hear it for Erica. [whoops]

640
00:28:19.804 --> 00:28:21.178
There you go. sweetheart.

641
00:28:23.178 --> 00:28:25.594
- [laughs] Hey. everybody.
- Sorry. man. let me. uh...

642
00:28:25.595 --> 00:28:27.552
Uh. so this song means a lot to me.

643
00:28:27.553 --> 00:28:29.219
- Sorry. Erica. Can I...?
- Oh.

644
00:28:29.220 --> 00:28:30.678
Can I...? You don't mind.

645
00:28:30.679 --> 00:28:32.219
Tom Petty. "Listen to Her Heart."

646
00:28:32.220 --> 00:28:33.886
Okay? Yeah.

647
00:28:33.887 --> 00:28:35.886
- You don't mind. do you?
- No. it's fine. Yeah.

648
00:28:35.887 --> 00:28:37.219
You can go on the next one.

649
00:28:37.220 --> 00:28:38.678
- Sure. Next time.
- Please.

650
00:28:38.679 --> 00:28:42.302
[Tom Petty's "Listen
to Her Heart" playing]

651
00:28:42.303 --> 00:28:45.969
♪ You think you're gonna take her away ♪

652
00:28:45.970 --> 00:28:50.052
♪ With your money and your cocaine ♪

653
00:28:50.053 --> 00:28:53.636
♪ Keep thinkin' that her
mind is gonna change ♪

654
00:28:53.637 --> 00:28:56.928
♪ But I know everything is okay ♪

655
00:28:56.929 --> 00:28:59.594
♪ She's gonna listen to her heart ♪

656
00:28:59.595 --> 00:29:01.636
[mouthing]

657
00:29:01.637 --> 00:29:04.177
♪ It's gonna tell her what to do ♪

658
00:29:04.178 --> 00:29:07.427
♪ She might need a lot of lovin' ♪

659
00:29:07.428 --> 00:29:09.219
♪ But she don't need... ♪

660
00:29:09.220 --> 00:29:10.887
[groans]

661
00:29:15.370 --> 00:29:16.887
What the fuck?

662
00:29:21.302 --> 00:29:23.301
Feeling better?

663
00:29:23.302 --> 00:29:25.220
Oh. my God.

664
00:29:26.813 --> 00:29:29.636
You weren't super specific
about what you wanted.

665
00:29:29.637 --> 00:29:32.678
so I sort of got one of everything.

666
00:29:32.679 --> 00:29:34.427
[Noah] What the...?

667
00:29:34.428 --> 00:29:36.053
How did we...?

668
00:29:38.133 --> 00:29:39.733
What are we doing here?

669
00:29:39.734 --> 00:29:42.344
It was an honor and a privilege

670
00:29:42.345 --> 00:29:44.803
to watch you work.

671
00:29:44.804 --> 00:29:48.135
We're like Kerouac and Burroughs.

672
00:29:48.136 --> 00:29:49.281
Who's who. do you think?

673
00:29:49.282 --> 00:29:50.761
I mean. obviously you're Kerouac.

674
00:29:50.762 --> 00:29:52.344
But I'll take Burroughs.

675
00:29:52.345 --> 00:29:53.636
I'll take that.

676
00:29:53.637 --> 00:29:55.637
Work? What do you mean. work?

677
00:29:56.512 --> 00:29:58.637
You were a surgeon. man.

678
00:30:00.119 --> 00:30:01.427
Wait. what time is it?

679
00:30:01.428 --> 00:30:02.993
Like. six.

680
00:30:02.994 --> 00:30:05.302
Haven't stayed up all
night since college.

681
00:30:05.303 --> 00:30:06.970
It's invigorating.

682
00:30:08.053 --> 00:30:09.970
[shudders]

683
00:30:11.260 --> 00:30:12.328
Here.

684
00:30:12.329 --> 00:30:15.386
- I already paid.
- No. no. it's fine.

685
00:30:15.387 --> 00:30:16.929
See you. man.

686
00:30:23.029 --> 00:30:24.253
Hi. Noah.

687
00:30:24.254 --> 00:30:27.312
So. I'm sorry. but I can't
let you on set today.

688
00:30:27.313 --> 00:30:28.678
What are you talking about?

689
00:30:28.679 --> 00:30:30.427
I guess Mr. Mann wants to limit

690
00:30:30.428 --> 00:30:32.651
the number of people on set
from this point forward.

691
00:30:32.652 --> 00:30:34.803
Just get on your radio
thing and call Mr. Mann

692
00:30:34.804 --> 00:30:36.624
and tell him to come
talk to me face-to-face.

693
00:30:36.625 --> 00:30:37.928
I can't. He's shooting.

694
00:30:37.929 --> 00:30:39.177
Yeah. I know. I-I got a rewrite

695
00:30:39.178 --> 00:30:40.678
for the scene he's shooting right now.

696
00:30:40.679 --> 00:30:41.761
so I need to get it to him.

697
00:30:41.762 --> 00:30:43.135
Oh. that's okay. He already has it.

698
00:30:43.136 --> 00:30:46.344
No. he... What? No. Wha... What?

699
00:30:46.345 --> 00:30:48.233
Yeah. the new pages
came out this morning.

700
00:30:48.234 --> 00:30:49.844
They're shooting them right now.

701
00:30:49.845 --> 00:30:53.386
[hypnotic. suspenseful music]

702
00:30:53.387 --> 00:30:55.469
Okay. you fucking call
him. Call him now.

703
00:30:55.470 --> 00:30:57.052
Call him on the radio now.

704
00:30:57.053 --> 00:30:58.844
Look at me and call...

705
00:30:58.845 --> 00:31:00.636
Call them on the fucking radio now!

706
00:31:00.637 --> 00:31:03.552
Call him now! Fucking call him.

707
00:31:03.553 --> 00:31:06.052
Jesus. this is the fucking rewrite here!

708
00:31:06.053 --> 00:31:07.470
Now get him out here!

709
00:31:10.239 --> 00:31:12.154
- _
- [easy listening music playing]

710
00:31:12.155 --> 00:31:13.446
[Margaret] Excuse me.

711
00:31:14.220 --> 00:31:17.511
This yolk is broken. I'd
like to send it back.

712
00:31:17.512 --> 00:31:19.052
Right away. ma'am.

713
00:31:19.053 --> 00:31:20.552
[exhales]

714
00:31:20.553 --> 00:31:22.427
Does this look moldy to you?

715
00:31:22.428 --> 00:31:23.844
- The napkin?
- You know.

716
00:31:23.845 --> 00:31:25.844
I'm very allergic to mold.

717
00:31:25.845 --> 00:31:27.219
What is that right there?

718
00:31:27.220 --> 00:31:28.594
Uh. it just looks like ketchup.

719
00:31:28.595 --> 00:31:30.636
Can't have mold in my lap.

720
00:31:30.637 --> 00:31:32.094
I'll break out in hives.

721
00:31:32.095 --> 00:31:34.383
Excuse me. Excuse me. please.

722
00:31:34.384 --> 00:31:36.552
Mom. is. is everything okay?

723
00:31:36.553 --> 00:31:38.164
I'm fine. why?

724
00:31:38.165 --> 00:31:40.091
You just seem a little tense.

725
00:31:40.092 --> 00:31:41.951
I'm very worried about you.

726
00:31:41.952 --> 00:31:43.557
I wanted to do something nice for you.

727
00:31:43.558 --> 00:31:45.594
Well. this is a very nice place.

728
00:31:45.595 --> 00:31:47.079
- Thank you.
- Do you think so?

729
00:31:47.080 --> 00:31:49.177
Shirley Divets said it
was the best restaurant

730
00:31:49.178 --> 00:31:51.886
in Los Angeles. but she
hasn't been out of Hyannis

731
00:31:51.887 --> 00:31:53.719
in 30 years. so what does she know?

732
00:31:53.720 --> 00:31:54.949
Excuse me.

733
00:31:58.303 --> 00:31:59.479
How's Dad?

734
00:32:00.506 --> 00:32:01.972
Why do you ask?

735
00:32:02.699 --> 00:32:04.010
Um...

736
00:32:04.011 --> 00:32:05.928
because I know he
doesn't usually like it

737
00:32:05.929 --> 00:32:07.386
when you're away.

738
00:32:07.387 --> 00:32:08.844
And you've been here for a while.

739
00:32:08.845 --> 00:32:10.552
so I'm just wondering how he's doing.

740
00:32:10.553 --> 00:32:12.457
[exhales sharply]

741
00:32:12.458 --> 00:32:15.212
That's actually something I
wanted to discuss with you.

742
00:32:17.720 --> 00:32:19.637
[exhales] I think it's time I go home.

743
00:32:21.720 --> 00:32:22.798
Oh.

744
00:32:23.565 --> 00:32:25.391
Well. I mean. if you think it's time.

745
00:32:25.392 --> 00:32:28.594
I hate the idea of
leaving you here alone

746
00:32:28.595 --> 00:32:31.135
in this extraordinarily
vulnerable state.

747
00:32:31.136 --> 00:32:33.636
Actually. I've been feeling
a little bit better lately.

748
00:32:33.637 --> 00:32:36.220
- So...
- But your father has dementia.

749
00:32:38.428 --> 00:32:39.719
What?

750
00:32:39.720 --> 00:32:42.719
And he's... lost all our money.

751
00:32:42.720 --> 00:32:44.928
- What?
- Excuse me.

752
00:32:44.929 --> 00:32:46.636
- What?
- Ma'am?

753
00:32:46.637 --> 00:32:49.177
This napkin is covered in mold.

754
00:32:49.178 --> 00:32:51.470
I'd like another. A clean one.

755
00:32:52.553 --> 00:32:54.292
[waiter] Of course. ma'am.

756
00:32:54.293 --> 00:32:55.511
I'm going to have a talk

757
00:32:55.512 --> 00:32:57.219
with Shirley Divets when I get back.

758
00:32:57.220 --> 00:33:00.011
Tell her she's too old to
be making recommendations.

759
00:33:00.012 --> 00:33:01.719
She thinks. just because she slept

760
00:33:01.720 --> 00:33:04.302
with Warren Beatty in '67.
she's an authority on every...

761
00:33:04.303 --> 00:33:06.678
[stammers] No. no. no. stop.
stop. stop. What... Okay.

762
00:33:06.679 --> 00:33:08.679
What. what do you mean Dad has dementia?

763
00:33:09.649 --> 00:33:12.246
- Alzheimer's. darling. I think.
- Well. how do you know?

764
00:33:12.247 --> 00:33:14.424
He gets confused. he forgets things.

765
00:33:14.425 --> 00:33:17.005
- So do I.
- It's not the same thing.

766
00:33:17.006 --> 00:33:19.047
The other day. he
couldn't find his keys.

767
00:33:19.048 --> 00:33:21.436
So what? I can never find my car keys.

768
00:33:21.437 --> 00:33:23.602
They were in his hand. Helen.

769
00:33:24.370 --> 00:33:25.615
It's just...

770
00:33:26.649 --> 00:33:28.259
he didn't know what they were.

771
00:33:28.260 --> 00:33:29.942
He didn't know what they were for.

772
00:33:35.261 --> 00:33:37.550
Uh. how long has this been going on?

773
00:33:38.211 --> 00:33:40.188
For a while. About a year.

774
00:33:40.189 --> 00:33:41.615
And you didn't tell me?

775
00:33:42.661 --> 00:33:45.025
You had a lot of things to worry about.

776
00:33:46.650 --> 00:33:48.644
Oh. my God. it never ends.

777
00:33:48.645 --> 00:33:50.260
[chuckling] I know.

778
00:33:50.261 --> 00:33:52.093
It feels like that
