Oh. yeah?

1294
00:55:13.488 --> 00:55:15.135
What were you doing out there?

1295
00:55:15.136 --> 00:55:16.595
I'm a coastal engineer.

1296
00:55:17.629 --> 00:55:19.094
How's that going?

1297
00:55:19.095 --> 00:55:20.546
Not well.

1298
00:55:21.136 --> 00:55:24.094
♪ And I had too much caffeine ♪

1299
00:55:24.095 --> 00:55:26.969
♪ And I was thinkin' 'bout myself... ♪

1300
00:55:26.970 --> 00:55:28.151
[receiver beeps]

1301
00:55:28.152 --> 00:55:30.172
- Have a good one.
- Thanks for the tip. Jim.

1302
00:55:30.173 --> 00:55:32.719
♪ In platform double suede ♪

1303
00:55:32.720 --> 00:55:35.844
♪ Yeah. there she was... ♪

1304
00:55:35.845 --> 00:55:37.554
Can I ask you a question?

1305
00:55:37.555 --> 00:55:39.060
Shoot.

1306
00:55:39.061 --> 00:55:40.820
What's with the electricity out here?

1307
00:55:40.821 --> 00:55:42.844
Is the grid completely off?

1308
00:55:42.845 --> 00:55:45.145
No. Just ever since the last hurricane.

1309
00:55:45.146 --> 00:55:46.554
they only turn it on
between nine and five.

1310
00:55:46.555 --> 00:55:48.678
We got our own battery bank. though.

1311
00:55:48.679 --> 00:55:51.135
This place used to be so beautiful.

1312
00:55:51.136 --> 00:55:52.761
Yeah. well. there aren't enough of us

1313
00:55:52.762 --> 00:55:54.065
out here to matter anymore.

1314
00:55:54.066 --> 00:55:55.564
We can't afford those wind turbines

1315
00:55:55.565 --> 00:55:57.434
they got out in East Hampton. so...

1316
00:55:57.435 --> 00:55:58.605
Right.

1317
00:56:05.061 --> 00:56:06.512
[bartender] You here for work?

1318
00:56:08.126 --> 00:56:09.552
I am.

1319
00:56:09.553 --> 00:56:11.220
Oh.

1320
00:56:12.646 --> 00:56:14.194
How much do I owe you?

1321
00:56:15.294 --> 00:56:16.748
It's on the house.

1322
00:56:18.439 --> 00:56:21.420
I haven't seen a face like
yours out here in a while.

1323
00:56:22.953 --> 00:56:24.387
I like it.

1324
00:56:25.887 --> 00:56:27.928
[tense music]

1325
00:56:27.929 --> 00:56:31.095
[both moaning]

1326
00:56:32.220 --> 00:56:34.261
Yeah.

1327
00:56:36.552 --> 00:56:39.714
- [gasps] Tighter.
- What?

1328
00:56:39.715 --> 00:56:40.761
[Joanie grunts]

1329
00:56:40.762 --> 00:56:42.761
- Better?
- [grunts. inhales sharply]

1330
00:56:42.762 --> 00:56:44.595
- What?
- [panting]

1331
00:56:46.702 --> 00:56:48.195
What's up?

1332
00:56:49.095 --> 00:56:50.386
It's not working for me.

1333
00:56:50.387 --> 00:56:51.552
What the fuck do you want?

1334
00:56:57.052 --> 00:56:59.134
You are one sick bitch.

1335
00:56:59.135 --> 00:57:01.261
♪♪♪

1336
00:57:25.887 --> 00:57:27.631
[Joanie] Stop.

1337
00:57:27.632 --> 00:57:29.387
[gasps]

1338
00:57:30.303 --> 00:57:32.135
[moaning]

1339
00:57:32.136 --> 00:57:33.984
- [bartender] Oh. yeah.
- [Joanie moans]

1340
00:57:33.985 --> 00:57:41.985
